<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Python on MCP Toolbox for Databases</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/documentation/connect-to/toolbox-sdks/python-sdk/</link><description>Recent content in Python on MCP Toolbox for Databases</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/documentation/connect-to/toolbox-sdks/python-sdk/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>ADK</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/documentation/connect-to/toolbox-sdks/python-sdk/adk/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/documentation/connect-to/toolbox-sdks/python-sdk/adk/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="overview"&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;toolbox-adk&lt;/code&gt; package provides a Python interface to the MCP Toolbox service, enabling you to load and invoke tools from your own applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="installation"&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;pip install google-adk&lt;span class="o"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;toolbox&lt;span class="o"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="usage"&gt;Usage&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The primary entry point is the &lt;code&gt;ToolboxToolset&lt;/code&gt;, which loads tools from a remote Toolbox server and adapts them for use with ADK agents.&lt;/p&gt;
